      <body>
         <div type="entry">
                <head>Diosqoros of Gozarto</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Diosqoros-of-Gozarto</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/182</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">173</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="129"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/243</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">
                        <abbr>Bp.</abbr> and author.<note>brief</note>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(13th/14th <abbr>cent.</abbr>) [<abbr>Syr. Orth.</abbr>]</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>
                        <abbr>Bp.</abbr> and author. Born in <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Bartelle">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/260">Barṭelle</placeName>
                        </ref>, his
                        baptismal name was Gabriel. He was consecrated <abbr>bp.</abbr> of Gozarto d-Qardu
                        (Cizre) in 1285/6. He was the author of a verse biography of <ref rend="bold"
                       target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Bar-Ebroyo-Grigorios">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/239">Bar ʿEbroyo</persName>
                        </ref> and of his brother <ref rend="bold"
                       target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Barsawmo-Safi-Grigorios">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/245">Barṣawmo Ṣafī</persName>
                        </ref> and of an Anaphora preserved in several <abbr>mss.</abbr> (not
                        yet published).</p>
                </div>
                <div type="bibl">
                    <head>Sources</head>
                    <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Barsoum, <title rend="italic">Scattered pearls</title>,
                            485–86.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Y.  Çiçek (<abbr>ed.</abbr>), <title rend="italic">Diosqoros d-Gozarto. Mimro ʿal
                                qadišo Grigoriyos maphryono d-hu Bar ʿEbroyo</title> (Glane/Losser,
                            1985).</bibl>
                        <bibl>E.  Renaudot, <title rend="italic">Liturgiarum Orientalium
                                Collectio</title>, vol. 2 (1847), 489–504. (<abbr>LT</abbr> of the
                            Anaphora)</bibl>
                        <bibl>H.  Takahashi, ‘A mimro on Maphrian Gregory Barṣawmo Ṣafī Bar ʿEbroyo
                            by Dioscorus Gabriel of Barṭelli, Bishop of Gozarto d-Qardu’, in <title rend="italic">The Syriac Renaissance</title>, <abbr>ed.</abbr> H. Teule <abbr>et al.</abbr>
                            (<abbr>ECS</abbr> 9; 2010), 151–94.</bibl>
                    </listBibl>
                </div>
